    "id": 440,
    "text": "22. Re-assessment/Re-checking of Papers. Re-assessment/re-checking of papers means a re-evaluation of answer(s) already checked/evaluated by the examiners. Answer books of a student, in any exam, will not be reassessed under any circumstances. The rechecking procedure will be carried out according to instructions mentioned in Annex B. 23. Issuance of Academic Transcript/Detailed Marks Sheet. A student desirous of obtaining Academic Transcript/Detailed Marks Sheet may apply to Controller of Examinations NUST through their own institution along with the prescribed fee, as per the policy issued on the subject. 24. Issuance of MS Degree before Convocation. A student desirous of obtaining an MS degree before convocation may apply to NUST Main Office (Registrar Dte) through their own institution or directly with the prescribed fee. MS degree can be collected through any person by providing an authority letter of the student. 25. Issuance of Certificates. Different types of certificates may be obtained from Main",
