    "text": "3. Scheme of Studies 1 The assessment scheme shall be as follows: Nature of Examination Duration Frequency End semester examination 3 hours 1 Mid Term 2 hours 1 Quizzes Minimum: 3 Class Participation Assignments / Project(s) / Own time Case Studies *Shall be allocated only if there are no case studies. b. c. Weighting (%age) 30 \u2013 50 15 \u2013 25 05 \u2013 15 0 \u2013 5* 10 \u2013 40 The assessment scheme for EMBA shall be as follows: (1) In-class experiential activity (30-35%) (2) Project/Assignment/ Quiz (30-35%) (3) Midterm (optional) (10-15%) (4) Final (20-30%) The performance of each student in a course of study will be graded as: Grades Numerical Grade Grade Points A B+ B C+ C F I W 4.0 3.50 3.0 2.50 2.00 0.00 Incomplete Dropped Q Qualified T Transfer 0.00 (F Grade due to shortage of attendance) XF d. University follows a relative grading system.",
