    "text": "University community leading to or inciting others to disrupt scheduled and/or normal activities within any campus building or area. r. Political/Sectarian Activities. Indulgence in political/ethnic/racial/sectarian activities or taking membership of any banned organization and participation in such like organizations for furthering the cause of a political party. s. Harassment. It covers the following: (1) Passing remarks, placing visual or written material, aimed at a specific person or group: (a) with the intention of causing harm to the person or group; and/or, (b) creating an environment that limits a student's educational opportunity. (2) Making unwanted verbal or physical advances or explicit derogatory statements toward individuals, that cause them discomfort or humiliation or that interfere with their educational opportunity. (3) Physical assault t. Gambling. Unauthorized and/or illegal exchange of money favours or services as a result of an organized or unorganized game or competition. u. Smoking. NUST H-12 campus has been declared",
