    "text": "t. Gambling. Unauthorized and/or illegal exchange of money favours or services as a result of an organized or unorganized game or competition. u. Smoking. NUST H-12 campus has been declared green campus; therefore, smoking is prohibited on University premises for which a policy directive has been issued. v. Abuse of the Student Conduct System. Abusing the student conduct system includes, but is not limited to: w. (1) failure to obey the notice from a University official to appear for a meeting or hearing as part of the student conduct system; (2) falsification, distortion, or misrepresentation of information before a hearing body or designated hearing officer of the University; (3) disruption or interference with the orderly conduct of a hearing proceeding; (4) causing a violation of the University Code of Conduct hearing to convene in bad faith; Public Display of Affection (PDA). Indecent behaviour exhibited on the campus including classes, cafeteria,",
