    "text": "Figure 1: Complaint Process c. SGC: Filing Process and Procedure. If the individual\u2019s complaint remains unresolved till the expiry of the stipulated timeframe in Figure 1, the student may approach the Student Grievance Committee (SGC) through a written application/email to the Head of SGC. In exceptional cases, the student can also approach the committee directly. The responsibility for the decision to directly approach the SGC rests with the student. Similarly, a student can withdraw a grievance at any stage of the process by sending a written request to the Head of the SGC. Once withdrawn, the grievance will not be reinstituted, unless a change in the circumstances has occurred. d. Composition of SGC (1) Head (1x Senior Faculty) (2) 2 x Faculty Members (3) 1 x F3H (Co-opted member, when a female student agrees to report the issue to SGC) e. Duration of the Grievance Redressal. Generally, the SGC is",
