    "id": 624,
    "text": "11. Discipline. The best state of discipline is expected from the residents, a few aspects of the discipline are highlighted here: a. Ragging. Ragging, in any shape, that can cause physical or psychological harm or raises apprehension of fear, shame, or an embarrassment to the new student, including teasing, abusing, shouting, playing practical jokes, or causing harm to the student or asking new students to do any act or to perform acts (which such student will not be willing to do ordinarily) is strictly forbidden. It is expected that senior students will help the juniors in their settling down process. Anybody found involved in ragging will be dealt with sternly. b. Smoking. University is a smoke-free zone. Smoking is prohibited in the rooms as well as in the hostel premises. c. Criminal/Unlawful Activities. Following will be considered unlawful activity: (1) Joining banned organizations or involvement in anti-state activities. (2) Creating",
